step 1, get [[git]] (looks like you should omit gentoos gitolite)
step 2, get [[ruby]]
step 3, get [[sudo]]

set python 2.7 as default....
{{Cmd|sudo eselect python set 1}}
{{Cmd|sudo /etc/init.d/git-daemon start}}
{{Cmd|sudo useradd -s /sbin/nologin gitlab}}
{{Cmd|sudo mkdir /home/gitlab}}
{{Cmd|sudo chown gitlab:gitlab /home/gitlab}}
{{Cmd|sudo gpasswd -a gitlab git}}
{{Cmd|sudo -u gitlab -H ssh-keygen -t rsa -f /home/gitlab/.ssh/id_rsa}}
{{Cmd|cd /home/git}}
{{Cmd|sudo -u git -H git clone -b gl-v320 https://github.com/gitlabhq/gitolite.git /home/git/gitolite}}
{{Cmd|sudo -u git -H mkdir /home/git/bin}}
cmd dont like this, so run:  sudo -u git -H sh -c 'printf "%b\n%b\n" "PATH=\$PATH:/home/git/bin" "export PATH" >> /home/git/.profile'
{{Cmd|sudo -u git -H sh -c 'gitolite/install -ln /home/git/bin'}}
{{Cmd|sudo cp /home/gitlab/.ssh/id_rsa.pub /home/git/gitlab.pub}}
{{Cmd|sudo chmod 0444 /home/git/gitlab.pub}}
cmd dont like this either so run: sudo -u git -H sh -c "PATH=/home/git/bin:$PATH; gitolite setup -pk /home/git/gitlab.pub"
{{Cmd|sudo chmod 750 /home/git/.gitolite/}}
{{Cmd|sudo chown -R git:git /home/git/.gitolite/}}
{{Cmd|sudo chmod -R ug+rwXs,o-rwx /home/git/repositories/}}
{{Cmd|sudo chown -R git:git /home/git/repositories/}}
{{Cmd|sudo -u gitlab -H ssh git@localhost}}
test make SURE git is running, if git daemon is not running this will catastrophically crash your system
{{Cmd|sudo -u gitlab -H git clone git@localhost:gitolite-admin.git /tmp/gitolite-admin}}
delete test garbage
{{Cmd|sudo rm -rf /tmp/gitolite-admin}}

